"{\"uid\": \"jdsupra.com-legalnews-2024-summer-olympics-series-the-4401014\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"[co-author: Maria Ishaq]* Almost a century ago, in 1928, the Olympic Games were held in Amsterdam.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14, \"end\": 19, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"score\": 0.9999931193208591, \"rank\": 4.555407097586122e-06, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\"}, {\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac\", \"score\": 0.9965780283571398, \"rank\": 0.0034229804990707565, \"text\": \"Ishaq\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac\"}, {\"begin\": 91, \"end\": 100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 0.9998159289588731, \"rank\": 0.000182875141295368, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 57, \"to\": 74}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the Netherlands has not been particularly active when it comes to organizing this major event as it has not organized the Olympics since, Dutch lawmakers certainly have not taken a step back.\", \"from\": 102, \"to\": 302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9951069485622014, \"rank\": 0.0027071491891874164, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 249, \"end\": 254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9891341390228673, \"rank\": 0.0053231107799889986, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this major event\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"a step\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Significant changes have been made to our employment laws, one of which could possibly be considered the most transformative-namely, the introduction of the \\\"preventive dismissal assessment.\\\"\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Significant changes\", \"from\": 303, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"our employment laws\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 360}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 452}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"preventive dismissal assessment\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 492}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch dismissal laws during the time of the Amsterdam Olympics used to heavily prioritize freedom of contract.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 496, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9891341390228673, \"rank\": 0.0053231107799889986, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 540, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 0.9998159289588731, \"rank\": 0.000182875141295368, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 532}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"contract\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 605}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As is currently common in several countries, employers did not have to face many legal restrictions when deciding to dismiss an employee; they were merely required to take a certain notice period into account.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several countries\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"many legal restrictions\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 706}, {\"ngram\": \"an employee\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 743}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain notice period\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"account\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the termination of their employment contract, employees would be able to enforce their rights only by initiating legal proceedings.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the termination\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"their employment contract\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"their rights\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"legal proceedings\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1945 these principles changed with the introduction of the preventive dismissal assessment.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these principles\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 980}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"the preventive dismissal assessment\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From this point on, unilateral terminations by employers could occur only after prior, governmental review of whether the proposed dismissal is reasonable.\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1066}, {\"ngram\": \"unilateral terminations\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"prior, governmental review\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"the proposed dismissal\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the present time, the following conditions apply when an employee does not agree with their dismissal: Without the required permission, a dismissal cannot be legally valid.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the present time\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"the following conditions\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1253}, {\"ngram\": \"an employee\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"their dismissal\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the required permission\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1345}, {\"ngram\": \"a dismissal\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In such cases, an employee can ask the sub-district court to undo the dismissal.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1465, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such cases\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"an employee\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"the sub-district court\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the dismissal\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The employment contract will continue to exist and wages must continue to be paid.\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The employment contract\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1489}, {\"ngram\": \"wages\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, the nature of Dutch dismissal law is unique in a way that it is highly protective.\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1573, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9891341390228673, \"rank\": 0.0053231107799889986, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nature\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Employers need a reasonable ground for dismissal and cannot unilaterally terminate the employment agreement without the prior consent of UWV or the sub-district court.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Employers\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"a reasonable ground\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"dismissal\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"the employment agreement\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"the prior consent\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"UWV\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1782}, {\"ngram\": \"the sub-district court\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u200b1Littler's International Guide discusses more than 90 workplace law topics in over 45 countries/territories, including jurisdictions in every region of the world.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u200b1Littler's International Guide\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 90 workplace law topics\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"over 45 countries/territories\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"jurisdictions\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"every region\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information on the International Guide, please contact your Littler attorney or KM - Managing Editor/PublicationsKristen Countryman.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Knowledge_management\", \"score\": 0.9999999998096882, \"rank\": 1.5484023075902558e-10, \"text\": \"KM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Knowledge_management\", \"dbpedia\": 